description.__cdata:
This town while VERY small in size has about five or six Federal Signal 2001-130's scattered all throughout the town. Towards the center of this town stands to what it appears a refurbished sentry siren (Model: 10v) during the tornado that destroyed the town.

Was a depressing sight to see this town torn to absolute bits.

description.__cdata: Sorta looks like a Allertor, but isn't.

http://stocktonkansas.net/CC%20MInutes-112007.doc

http://stocktonkansas.net/CC%20Minutes-120407.doc

Town apparently has a few sirens to use. Possible new sirens from the region is was bought from might be ASC products. Street view is not updated with these new sirens. Current sirens in this town are an FS xt22 and a WPS2905 from Whelen.
